    <main>
        <section id="intro">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>Dr. A.P.J. Abdul Kalam, often referred to as the Missile Man of India, was a renowned scientist, visionary, and the 11th President of India. He played a crucial role in India's civilian space program and military missile development.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section id="achievements">
            <h2>Key Achievements</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Instrumental in the development of India's first satellite launch vehicle (SLV-III).</li>
                <li>Chief Scientific Advisor to the Prime Minister of India.</li>
                <li>Played a pivotal role in the Pokhran-II nuclear tests.</li>
                <li>Authored several books, including "Wings of Fire" and "Ignited Minds."</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section id="legacy">
            <h2>Legacy</h2>
            <p>Dr. Kalam's legacy lives on through his inspirational speeches, books, and his vision for India's growth through education and technology. He is remembered as a people's president who connected with citizens, especially the youth, and encouraged them to dream big.</p>
        </section>
